Class Configuration

java.lang.Object
  cz.cvut.felk.cig.jcop.problem.Configuration
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.lang.Comparable<Configuration>
public class Configuration
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Comparable<Configuration>

Configuration is representation of one state in state space. It has configuration attributes, dimension and history of operations applied to this configuration.

Configuration

public Configuration(java.util.List<java.lang.Integer> attributes,
                     java.lang.String createText)
Special constructor for creating first configuration (eg. starting configuration). DO NOT use in operations!

Is equivalent to new Configuration(attributes, new OperationHistory(new NewConfigurationOperation(createText))).

Parameters:
attributes - new attributes for Configuration. List is NOT copied so take care not to use it for more than one configuration or change it afterwards.
createText - text for NewConfigurationOperation constructor

fingerprint

public java.lang.String fingerprint()
Fingerprint is somehow similar to hashCode in that way, that two configurations that are considered equal via CompareTo has the same fingerprint. However, contrast to hashCode, if two configurations has the same fingerprint, they are considered equal.

Returns:
Fingerprint of configuration
